President Obama called King Abdullah of Saudi Arabia to express his condolences on the death of Crown Prince Nayif bin Abd al-Aziz Al Saud. The President also thanked Crown Prince Nayif for his contributions, particularly in building counterterrorism cooperation between the United States and Saudi Arabia. President Obama informed King Abdullah that a senior delegation, led by Secretary of Defense Panetta, has traveled to Jeddah to offer condolences in person during the official mourning period. Additionally, the President congratulated King Abdullah on the appointment of Prince Salman bin Abd al-Aziz Al Saud as the new Crown Prince.